Parliament, Monday, 17 August 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, will tomorrow have an interaction with the Polokwane Local Municipality, Limpopo’s MEC for Cooperative Governance, Office of the Auditor-General, South African Local Government Association (Salga), Department of Cooperative Governance, and Eskom, on the state of Polokwane Local Municipality.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: 18 August 2020
	Venue: Virtual
	Time: 9:00 – 12:00
	
	Later on, the committee will receive a briefing from the Limpopo Provincial Government on its Covid-19 response plans.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: 18 August 2020
	Venue: Virtual
	Time: 19:00-22:00
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COGTA, MS FAITH MUTHAMBI.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
